element.returns: DOM element for box (may be null)

marginBottom.returns: the used value for the bottom margin

marginLeft.returns: the used value for the left margin

marginRight.returns: the used value for the right margin

marginTop.returns: the used value for the top margin

BoxInfo.returns: The properties of a box, can be accessed after document conversion has finished - see The Box Tracking API.

getPrinceBoxes.returns: A list of JavaScript objects called boxes.

bind.desc: Defines a value for the this object, returns a new function.

debug.desc: only available when the --debug command-line option is specified.

info.desc: only available when the --verbose command-line option is specified.

NaN.desc: The special value Not a Number.

defineProperty.desc: Adds a property to the object and defines certain traits like enumerability.

arguments.name: description
arguments.desc: Optional second argument to describe the attachment.

arguments.name: filename
arguments.desc: Optional third argument to specify the filename to be displayed for the attachment in the PDF.

arguments.name: relationship
arguments.desc: Optional fourth argument to specify the AFRelationship value of the attachment.

objectStreams.desc: Can be used to disable PDF object streams.  Object streams are enabled by default.

arguments.desc: Note that Prince passes the provided values verbatim to the PDF viewer, so the user can supply values that Prince doesn't know about, but the viewer does.

pages.returns: A list of page boxes, can be accessed after document conversion has finished.

arguments.desc: One of the supported PDF profiles.

debug.desc: only available when the --debug command-line option is specified.

info.desc: only available when the --verbose command-line option is specified.

addEventListener.desc: can be called to listen to the complete event on the Prince object. See Event Handling.

addScriptFunc.desc: exposes an arbitrary JavaScript function to CSS. See Script Functions.

convertToBuffer.returns: ArrayBuffer if successful, null if not

arguments.name: JSON
arguments.desc: as specified in the Job description JSON;

pageCount.returns: Total number of document pages, can be accessed after document conversion has finished.

oncomplete.desc: The complete event is fired when all layout is finished (and after the last repeated layout, if this was requested), just before the PDF is output, so that it can cancel the PDF output by triggering a fail-safe if necessary, or log information about the PDF like the page count.

decodeURIComponent.desc: Decodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) component.

encodeURIComponent.desc: Encodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) component.

escape.desc: Computes a new string by replacing certain characters with a hexadecimal escape sequence.

eval.desc: Evaluates text as JavaScript source code.

hasOwnProperty.desc: Returns a boolean indicating whether the object has the specified property.

isFinite.desc: Determines whether the passed value is a finite number.

isNaN.desc: Checks if the argument's value is the special Not a Number value.

isPrototypeOf.desc: Checks if an object exists in another object's prototype chain.

parseFloat.desc: Turns input into a floating point number.

parseInt.desc: Turns input into an integer number.

arguments.name: radix
arguments.desc: Indicates number base, for example 10 to parse input as a decimal value, 16 for hex values.

propertyIsEnumerable.desc: Returns a Boolean indicating whether the specified property is enumerable.

toLocaleString.desc: Converts an object to a string with a language sensitive representation of said string.

toString.desc: Converts an object to a string.

unescape.desc: Computes a new string by replacing hexadecimal escape sequences with the characters they represent.

valueOf.desc: Returns the primitive value an object.
